        	<p>Obolo Chwerty is a simple Unicode keyboard for the Obolo language, using the CHWERTY layout <samp>ch</samp>, <samp>ọ</samp>, and <samp>n̄</samp>.</p> 
	<p>The keyboard uses CHWERTY layout.
<p>
"Ebi Obolo" do not have 'C' and 'H' in their "abiche" (alphabet), but they have the 'CH' sound (as well as the 'SH' sound in some dialect). 
<p>This and other features make Obolo Language unique. Hence this unique layout.
<p>
